President Biden delivered a speech at IBM Poughkeepsie in New York, highlighting the importance of domestic semiconductor production for economic and national security. He emphasized the need to invest in advanced manufacturing facilities to produce chips in America and create good-paying jobs. The President also discussed the CHIPS and Science Act, which aims to boost research and development funding and ensure that companies that receive federal funding for new technology produce their products in the United States. Biden emphasized the role of infrastructure in attracting investment and making the country more competitive globally. He expressed confidence in America's ability to lead in industries of the future and called for unity in achieving economic and national security goals.